### Description

I tried rewriting the code created by someone using the Svelte framework, it almost works like this. It's just that, there were several bugs that I got because I didn't understand Angular well, I created an Image component which received the height and width data from the app component. When the image size is larger than the limit, when ngOnInit, it will send data so that the parent updates the data so that the component receives the new data. But it wasn't the same as I expected. Please help, here is the code below.

file `app.component.html`.

```HTML
<image
  *ngIf="object.type === 'image'"
  [x]="object.x"
  [y]="object.y"
  [file]="object.file"
  [width]="object.width"
  [height]="object.height"
  [payload]="object.payload"
  [pageScale]="pagesScale[pIndex]"
  (delete)="deleteObject(object.id)"
  (update)="updateObject(object.id, $event)"
></image>
```

file `image.component.ts`

```TS
...
export class Image {
  public render(): void {
    const limit = 500;

    let scale = 1;

    this.canvas.nativeElement.width = this.width;
    this.canvas.nativeElement.height = this.height;

    this.canvas.nativeElement.getContext('2d')?.drawImage(this.payload, 0, 0);

    if (this.width > limit) {
      scale = limit / this.width;
    }

    if (this.height > limit) {
      scale = Math.min(scale, limit / this.height);
    }

    this.update.emit({
      width: this.width * scale,
      height: this.height * scale,
    });

    if (!['image/png'].includes(this.file.type)) {
      this.canvas.nativeElement.toBlob((blob) => {
        this.update.emit({ file: blob });
      });
    }
  }

  public ngOnInit(): void {}

  public ngOnChanges(): void {}

  public ngDoCheck(): void {}

  public ngAfterViewInit(): void {
    this.render();
  }
}
```

